txt.en: 'Thank you, my forest friends, for your assistance.'
'The Ungoledain have taken Rhosgobel!'
'No, no, these are not Beornings [placeholder], these are bears.'
'I can not raise a sword against them but you can.'
'Quickly now, go and reclaim Rhosgobel while I search for some assistance!'
Instance: Heeding the Call
'Over here, my friend!'
'This way!'
'They approach!'
'No! What have you done to me?!'
'Keep her busy and all shall become clear!'
'Ugh, it was all so clear! Now, there is nothing.'
'What has been given, has been taken away!'
Ungoladan Warrior
'I can no longer hear the call of Mam Murgwid.'
'What I should have done long ago. I have taken away the gift you stole.'
'Listen my brood, we must retreat!'
'I saw the truth, it is not this place!'
'Mam Murgwid asks us to travel further south.'
'She waits at a mountain of shadow! We must leave!'
'What are you doing?! Are you listening to me?!'
'No, no! Argh!'
Ungoledain guard the path ahead
More Ungoledain patrol both sides of the old Elf bridge
Ungoledain have taken hold of Radagast's cottage!
Radagast wishes to speak with you outside his cottage
'What is this?!'
'Why do you impede our only desire?!'
'You will die for your actions.'
'This place is sacred, says Mam Murgwid!'
'We have heeded the call! Yet it still pulls?!'
'Something is not right! Mam Murgwid speak to me!'
'What have you done?!'
'No longer may you change your skin.'
'You shall stay here no longer. Leave my home.'
